│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                      │
│ The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM SLP vectorizer. The crash is due to an assertion failure, `trying to erase      │
│ instruction with users`, which happens during horizontal reduction vectorization.                                            │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ My analysis of the reproducer shows that the vectorizer identifies a chain of `xor` instructions as a candidate for          │
│ horizontal reduction. One of the operands in this chain, `%or92`, is also used by a PHI node, `%p1`, which is outside the    │
│ reduction chain. When the vectorizer attempts to transform the reduction, it tries to delete the original scalar instruction │
│ `%or92`. However, since `%p1` still uses `%or92`, the assertion fails.                                                       │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The correct fix is to add a safety check. Before vectorizing a horizontal reduction, the vectorizer must verify that no      │
│ instruction within the reduction candidate tree has users outside of that tree. If an external user is found, the vectorizer │
│ should abort the transformation for that candidate.                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ This check should be placed in the `HorizontalReduction::tryToReduce` function in `SLPVectorizer.cpp`, just before the call  │
│ to `vectorizeTree`. The logic involves iterating through the instructions in the `ReductionOps` map, collecting them into a  │
│ set, and then for each instruction, checking if any of its operands have users that are not in this set.                     │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ My previous attempts to apply this patch failed due to environmental issues with file modification. The most robust method,  │
│ which I will use now, is to modify the file directly in its pristine source location                                         │
│ (`/llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`) to ensure the build system uses the         │
│ corrected version. I will use a simple `sed` command to insert the code at the correct location.                             │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                      │
│ # Create a file with the patch content to avoid shell mangling issues.                                                       │
│ cat <<'EOF' > patch.txt                                                                                                      │
│   // Check if any of the reduction operands have external users.                                                             │
│   // TODO: We can be less conservative and try to remodel the use-def chain.                                                 │
│   SmallSet<Value *, 8> ReductionValues;                                                                                      │
│   for (const auto &pair : ReductionOps)                                                                                      │
│     ReductionValues.insert(pair.first);                                                                                      │
│   for (const auto &pair : ReductionOps) {                                                                                    │
│     for (Value *V : cast<Instruction>(pair.first)->operands()) {                                                             │
│       if (isa<Constant>(V))                                                                                                  │
│         continue;                                                                                                            │
│       for (User *U : V->users()) {                                                                                           │
│         if (!ReductionValues.count(U)) {                                                                                     │
│           LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Bailing out from horizontal reduction due to "                                          │
│                                "external user.\n");                                                                          │
│           return nullptr;                                                                                                    │
│         }                                                                                                                    │
│       }                                                                                                                      │
│     }                                                                                                                        │
│   }                                                                                                                          │
│ EOF                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ # Apply the patch directly to the true source file in the dependency directory.                                              │
│ # This is the most reliable way to ensure the change is picked up by the build.                                              │
│ sed -i '18926r patch.txt' /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                       │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
